				 Saudi police arrest 208 militants
																								Riyadh, Nov. 28 (Reuters): Saudi Arabia said today it had arrested 208 people for involvement in several cells planning attacks on an oil installation as well as clerics and security forces.																								The state television said one of the cells was planning to smuggle missiles into the country.																								A cell of eight militants led by foreigners planned an attack on an oil facility in the Eastern Province, home to key oil installations. The report said 18 of those arrested belonged to a cell led by an expert in launching missiles who had infiltrated into the country. Another 22 were part of a group that plotted to assassinate clerics, it said. 
